title: For Sale:  French Military MLE 1892 Revolver Set - Mfg in 1899 - EXCELLENT
postcontent:
This is a French Military Model 1892 revolver chambered in the 8mm Lebel pistol cartridge. I bought it nearly 30 years ago from an older fellow who told me that his father brought it back from Europe after WWI. He had the story but no official documentation. I have however looked it over many times and there are no visible importer marks which does lend some credibility to his story, plus I felt like he was giving me the straight scoop at the time.

This revolver was produced in 1899 making it about 116 years old and all I can say is that it's in terrific condition for being so old. Most of the original blued finish is intact and the hammer, trigger and loading gate still has a lot of their original "straw" colors. There is some thinning of the bluing around the muzzle and a few freckles on the frame, but I'd put overall condition at around 90%.

The wood grips are excellent too with sharp checkering and no dings or cracks. The the bore and cylinders are in fine shape - shiny with strong rifling and without any rust or pitting. Everything functions mechanically just as it should.

Pistol comes with what I was told are it's original leather holster and lanyard which are in good condition given their age. Then there are two boxes of 8mm Lebel ammo by Fiocchi. This ammo is still produced but you do have to do some hunting to find it. I bought these two boxes a while ago at Sportsman Guide. Specs on ammo is 115 grain FMJ bullet at 880 FPS. So it's not a powerhouse by any means but it does have enough get up and go to get the job done.

Bottom line is that this is a very nice collectible that you don't see too often especially in this condition. It's a perfect addition to any military collection and especially so for those who specialize in French Militaria. 

Price is $650 for everything with pickup in the Brandon area. This revolver is 1 year shy of being a true antique by BATF definition so I won't ship it. Buyer must be at least 21 and a Florida resident.

title: For Sale:  $629 & UP!!!  H&K P2000SK & P2000 40S&W or 9mm
postcontent:
VISIT US AT www.GunsMidwest.com FOR THIS DEAL AND OTHER H&K CLOSEOUT MODELS!

Like the slightly larger P2000 model, the P2000 SK (subcompact) combines elements of the successful HK USP Compact pistol with recent technological innovations from HK engineers — only in a smaller, more concealable design.The P2000 SK is available with Law Enforcement Modification (also known as Combat Defense Action) trigger system introduced in 2001 on the USP Compact “LEM” (Law Enforcement Modification) model. This unique pre-cocked hammer system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull and short trigger travel from first to last round fired) with a double action hammer system. The LEM/CDA trigger pull has been reduced to 7.3 – 8.5 pounds of pressure (32.5 – 37.8 Newtons), compared to 12 – 15 pounds (53.4 – 66.7 N) found on many conventional double action pistols. Optional adjustment by an HK certified armorer can bring the trigger pull into the 5.5 pound (24.5 N) range.Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation — one that prevents unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third pull of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the Subcompact.

The enhanced LEM/CDA trigger system combines the reliability of a double-action revolver trigger with the crisp, precise trigger of a single-action pistol. For shooters that prefer a conventional double-action/single-action pistol, a double-action/single-action variant is also available with a decock button mounted on the rear of the frame. A choice of two simple-to-install grip panels make it easy to custom-fit the P2000 Subcompact to any shooter’s hand. And the same ambidextrous magazine release and dual slide release levers found on the P2000 make handling the Subcompact easy for both right- and left-handed shooters.

A set of abbreviated “industry standard” mounting rails on the P2000 SK enable lights, laser aimers, and other accessories to be added by sliding them onto the open rail system. The HK P2000 SK also can use widely available, reliable USP Compact magazines.

VISIT WWW.GUNSMIDWEST.COM FOR ALL H&K SPECIALS

FLAT RATE $14.95 SHIPPING ANYWHERE IN THE US & NO SALES TAX UNLESS FROM KANSAS

Like the slightly larger P2000 model, the P2000 SK (subcompact) combines elements of the successful HK USP Compact pistol with recent technological innovations from HK engineers — only in a smaller, more concealable design.The P2000 SK is available with Law Enforcement Modification (also known as Combat Defense Action) trigger system introduced in 2001 on the USP Compact “LEM” (Law Enforcement Modification) model. This unique pre-cocked hammer system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull and short trigger travel from first to last round fired) with a double action hammer system. The LEM/CDA trigger pull has been reduced to 7.3 – 8.5 pounds of pressure (32.5 – 37.8 Newtons), compared to 12 – 15 pounds (53.4 – 66.7 N) found on many conventional double action pistols. Optional adjustment by an HK certified armorer can bring the trigger pull into the 5.5 pound (24.5 N) range.Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation — one that prevents unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third pull of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the Subcompact.

The enhanced LEM/CDA trigger system combines the reliability of a double-action revolver trigger with the crisp, precise trigger of a single-action pistol. For shooters that prefer a conventional double-action/single-action pistol, a double-action/single-action variant is also available with a decock button mounted on the rear of the frame. A choice of two simple-to-install grip panels make it easy to custom-fit the P2000 Subcompact to any shooter’s hand. And the same ambidextrous magazine release and dual slide release levers found on the P2000 make handling the Subcompact easy for both right- and left-handed shooters.

A set of abbreviated “industry standard” mounting rails on the P2000 SK enable lights, laser aimers, and other accessories to be added by sliding them onto the open rail system. The HK P2000 SK also can use widely available, reliable USP Compact magazines.

title: For Sale:  Redfield 3-9 Golden 5 Star With Accu-Trac & Bullet Drop Compensator Gloss Black Excellent Condition
postcontent:
For sale; is a Redfield 3-9 Golden Five Star, with Accu-Trac, & a bullet drop compensator. This scope has a gloss black finish, & is in excellent condition. The lens are clear, & scratch free. The ring marks are minimal.

This scope has an A dial on it; which is by far the most popular dial.  We would substitute one of the other dials, if desired.

We can email close up photos, on request.

Shipping to the lower 48 states, will be $12.00. Please call: REDACTED, for a quote to Alaska, or Hawaii.

Although these Redfields were some of the best hunting scopes, ever built; at this point, they are almost 20 years old. We can not guarantee this scope is in perfect condition. Even if they look good, & there doesn't seem to be anything wrong with them, you don't know for sure, until you mount the scope, & try it.

However, we do guarantee, there is nothing obviously wrong with the scope, we don't tell you about.

I have well over a dozen Illuminators, just like this one. All of them have been disassembled, & cleaned; & they work good. All of these original Redfields, should be disassembled, & cleaned, before mounting them on a rifle. This usually costs about $60.00. You should figure that in, when buying the scope.

We have used several scope repair companies. The two we would absolutely NOT recommend, to anyone; are: Iron Sights, & ABO.

We have sent a couple Redfields to Iron Sights, & it took a year to get them back, & they still had the same problems, they had, when we sent them in.

ABO, is even worse. They either can't, or won't, fix anything properly, & they do not stand behind their work. They are very expensive; also. We would not recommend you send a toy scope, or a Tasco (same thing actually), to ABO; much less a prized Redfield, such as an Illuminator.

That said; there are several other scope repair companies; which are reputable; who will disassemble, & clean a Redfield.

We take all major credit cards, with a 3% surcharge. We will also take a check, but we will have to delay shipping for a couple days; on out-of-state checks.

We are a retail store, so our items are subject to sale BEFORE they are reserved online.

If you don’t see what you are looking for, please call us at REDACTED. We can sell most scopes at very reasonable prices.

Thank you.

Smith & Wesson Model of 1891
A total production of only 1,251, this beautiful unusual pistol combines the frame of a 38 single action 3rd Model with a single shot barrel. This pistol is a top break and functions exactly as a revolver does. The top of the barrel rib is marked with the two line, two block address/patent dates with "MODEL OF 91" in the center, the left side is marked "22 LONG RIFLE CTG" and the right side of the frame has the S&W Trade Mark logo. Blade front and notch rear sights, blue finish with casehardened hammer, trigger and trigger guard and fitted with brown checkered wooden grips.  they made very few with the Olympic chamber barrels in .22 caliber as they were used to shoot the Olympics with., and there are not many around like these. With the use of an Olympic chamber barrel you must seat the round down into the barrel lands to fire the gun. The cartridge seats easy to about the last 1/4" of it's length then you have to push it down hard for a final seat prior to firing it. This avoided bullet jump in a barrel and allowed for much more accuracy on Target.

 Description: 
 The Micro Might handgun is a five shot, fixed cylinder mini-revolver. It is designed around an historical and simple single action mechanism. By "fixed cylinder" means that the cylinder does not swing out of the frame for loading and unloading. Removal of the cylinder is accomplished by removing the cylinder base pin and taking the cylinder completely out of the frame. By "single action" means that the trigger performs only one function: it releases the hammer.
 Ammunition Warning
 Micro Might Inc. produces and sells Micro Might handguns designed and chambered for two different calibers. The intended caliber is noted both on the shipping and storage box and on the barrel of the Micro Might handgun itself. If your revolver is chambered for 22LR, any good quality factory made 22 caliber ammunition in long rifle, long or short may be safely used in the revolver. The revolver will also safely handle high velocity 22 ammunition.
 If your revolver is chambered for 22WMRF ammunition, ONLY USE 22WMRF cartridges. This designation stands for 22 caliber Winchester Magnum Rimfire ammunition. Use of standard 22 caliber ammunition in the 22WMRF revolvers can result in malfunctions and serious injuries.
